data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression tree no longer needed

The API now takes `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`. Your manual expression tree construction won't compile. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery can be deleted.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**Duplicate property names** across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) are now **uniquified** by appending a number. A migration will rename those columns.

**Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly to avoid a breaking migration:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, preserve the old shorter name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new parameter

Methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your custom logger won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Update **every** method in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
